.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt LOWDOWN_TERM_NEW 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm lowdown_term_new
.Nd allocate an ANSI-compatible terminal renderer
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb liblowdown
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/queue.h
.In stdio.h
.In lowdown.h
.Ft void *
.Fo lowdown_term_new
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
function allocates an ANSI-compatible, UTF-8 terminal renderer.
It must be freed with a call to
.Xr lowdown_term_free 3 .
The returned pointer may be used with multiple invocations of
.Xr lowdown_term_rndr 3 .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Always returns a valid pointer.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr lowdown 3
